Credit chain & third-party components
================================================================================

This product builds on the work of others. The AirPlay engine is a fork of
UxPlay and is therefore GPL-3.0; everything that links the engine inherits that
licence. The bundled/linked runtimes keep their own licences.

AirPlay protocol + GStreamer engine
  UxPlay — https://github.com/FDH2/UxPlay — GPL-3.0
    UxPlay descends from:
      RPiPlay      — https://github.com/FD-/RPiPlay        — GPL-3.0
      shairplay    — https://github.com/juhovh/shairplay   — (Juho Vähä-Herttua)
      playfair / openairplay — AirPlay reverse-engineering notes
    See UxPlay's own README for the complete upstream credit chain.

mDNS responder (used by the Windows dnssd shim)
  mjansson/mdns — https://github.com/mjansson/mdns — public domain (Unlicense)
    A self-contained RFC 6762 / 6763 mDNS responder, single header.

Media pipeline (dynamically linked / bundled as-is, not modified)
  GStreamer — https://gstreamer.freedesktop.org — LGPL-2.1
  GLib      — https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/glib — LGPL-2.1

Cryptography (pulled in by the engine)
  OpenSSL   — https://www.openssl.org — Apache-2.0

Rust crates (all permissive — MIT / Apache-2.0)
  tao, tray-icon, muda, eframe/egui, winit, raw-window-handle, windows-rs,
  x11 / x11rb, ureq (+ rustls), ed25519-compact, sha2, hex, zip, serde,
  serde_json, semver, dirs, image, anyhow. See each crate's own licence.

Apple Bonjour SDK (OPTIONAL Windows build dependency — NOT redistributed here)
  Proprietary. Only needed to build the optional Bonjour-proxy path of the
  Windows dnssd shim; the embedded-mdns path needs nothing from Apple. Bring
  your own SDK if you build that path. Never committed to this repository.

